 the sixth book in the The Chronicles of Narnia series by C.S. Lewis, Harfang is a city of giants in the far north. J.R.R Tolkien, the author of The Hobbit and The Lord of the Rings, gave the name Longbottom to one of the Hobbits' villages in the Shire, which is known for its pipe-weed.  Appearances Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix (film) (Black family tapestry) Notes and references   ↑ Black Family tree  ↑ Pottermore - The Black family tree  ↑ "Harfang" at Wiktionary     This article about a specific character is a stub. You can help by expanding it.            Categories         Categories:   Character stubs    British individuals    House of Black    Longbottom family    Males    Married individuals    Parents    Pure-bloods    Wizards             Languages      Deutsch Español Français Nederlands Polski Русский      *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click through and make a purchase. Community content is available under CC-BY-SA unless otherwise noted.             Advertisement     Fan Feed        More Harry Potter Wiki     1 Sirius Black     2 Hufflepuff     3 Ravenclaw                           Explore Wikis            Universal Conquest Wiki        Let's Go Luna! Wiki        Club 57 Wiki                              Explore properties          Fandom               Cortex RPG               Muthead               Futhead               Fanatical          Follow Us                                Overview          What is Fandom?               About               Careers               Press               Contact               Terms of Use               Privacy Policy               Global Sitemap               Local Sitemap            Community          Community Central               Support               Help               Do Not Sell My Info          Advertise          Media Kit               Fandomatic               Contact            Fandom Apps      Tak